65
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:52,872
Come out this way, Lionel.
No shame in therapy, is there, Althea?

66
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:55,679
Not at all. It takes guts, Lionel.

67
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:58,673
Maybe some of us don't need this crap.

68
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:03,309
And it's the Hubble Telescope,
not the Himball.

69
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:10,472
- Jeez, what an asshole!
- (SHE LAUGHS)

70
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,991
What do they want from me?

71
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,555
What have I done that's so wrong?

72
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:31,269
They act as if they don't have
their own peculiar things.

73
00:06:31,440 --> 00:06:35,991
Everybody's got something
they're not so proud of. Even you, probably.

74
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:40,039
- Me more than most.
- Why are they ganging up against me?

75
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:45,228
- I think they're worried about you.
- It's the kids. It isn't Jeremy.

76
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:51,077
He had nothing to do with my coming to you,
except pay. He's always willing to pay.

77
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:53,959
He's extremely generous.

78
00:06:56,280 --> 00:07:01,718
I am so humiliated that my own children
would threaten me.

79
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:03,996
How did they threaten you?

80
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:09,154
They said if I didn't get help,
they wouldn't deal with me any more.

81
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:14,957
- What do you think of that?
- Good kids.

82
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:28,633
- (MUMBLES)
- Hmm?

83
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:32,031
You must come to the house
for dinner on Thursday.

84
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:33,713
Really? You think so?

85
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:39,557
Yes. Jeremy will be home for the weekend,
and you can meet the kids.

86
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:50,430
How are you doing, Ainge?

87
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:53,319
- Evening, Lily.
- Hey, Doc.

88
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:55,471
Ainge.

89
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:20,835
<i>Tonight on "Unsolved Mysteries"... </i>

90
