653
00:54:03,080 --> 00:54:05,799
- You're in its grip.
- I never said that.

654
00:54:06,680 --> 00:54:08,671
Where's your wife, Henry?

655
00:54:12,280 --> 00:54:14,271
- Where's your wife?
- Go to hell.

656
00:54:14,440 --> 00:54:16,431
I didn't hear you.

657
00:54:16,600 --> 00:54:19,592
I thought we were talking about me.

658
00:54:24,800 --> 00:54:26,791
We got divorced.

659
00:54:30,440 --> 00:54:33,637
I had to get rid of her.
She couldn't satisfy me.

660
00:54:33,800 --> 00:54:35,392
What?

661
00:54:40,080 --> 00:54:42,514
I was never satisfied.

662
00:54:42,680 --> 00:54:44,875
Now we're back on track.

663
00:54:51,800 --> 00:54:54,268
- (MUMBLES)
- What's that?

664
00:54:58,040 --> 00:55:01,271
You are so mean.

665
00:55:18,640 --> 00:55:22,394
- That is such a wicked look.
- (DOC) What is it, Nessa?

666
00:55:22,560 --> 00:55:26,235
(NESSA) Look at those legs.
This chick is 12 feet tall!

667
00:55:26,400 --> 00:55:29,710
That's the body I'm getting. I've ordered it.

668
00:55:29,880 --> 00:55:33,589
Whoa! This dress
has to be surgically applied.

669
00:55:33,760 --> 00:55:36,593
Where is this beach
where everyone has good teeth?

670
00:55:36,760 --> 00:55:40,878
- What do you want me to see?
- Just chill for a second.

671
00:55:41,040 --> 00:55:45,397
Look at this guy. Gorgeous,
although clearly not of this earth.

672
00:55:45,560 --> 00:55:48,950
Excellent pecs, mutant cheekbones...

673
00:55:50,800 --> 00:55:56,272
Where are you going? I'm showing you
something. I just need to find the thing.

674
00:55:56,440 --> 00:56:01,036
- If you don't want a session, it's OK.
- I wanna have the session.

675
00:56:01,200 --> 00:56:06,399
I thought I'd show you things that interest
me. We could share, as they say.

676
00:56:06,560 --> 00:56:09,120
But I guess not, which we already knew.

677
00:56:09,280 --> 00:56:11,840
- What happened?
- What do you mean?

678
00:56:12,000 --> 00:56:16,915
- Did something happen at school?
- These appointments were not my idea.

679
00:56:17,080 --> 00:56:19,469
True. Should we stop them?

680
00:56:22,240 --> 00:56:25,835
I don't think
you know what you're talking about.

681
00:56:26,000 --> 00:56:32,155
This shrink school you went to,
did you hear about it on an infomercial?

682
00:56:41,440 --> 00:56:44,750
I wanna live in the world
that these people are in.

683
00:56:46,440 --> 00:56:52,754
No one ever says anything in there.
Have you noticed? So they're all very cool.

684
00:56:52,920 --> 00:56:55,309
Like they're all really deep.

685
00:56:56,360 --> 00:57:00,638
It's when people start talking
that everything goes to shit.

686
00:57:02,400 --> 00:57:05,551
There's this kid at school - Martin Brockett.

687
00:57:05,720 --> 00:57:10,032
He has some gigantic idea of himself
that no one else shares.

688
00:57:10,200 --> 00:57:15,115
You wouldn't believe the crap he lays on me.
Who appointed him my guide?

689
00:57:15,280 --> 00:57:20,912
If he has everything so figured out,
how come his best friend's a. 22 rifle?

690
00:57:22,520 --> 00:57:26,308
And why does he spend all his time
chasing after me?

691
00:57:26,480 --> 00:57:31,918
- Probably thinks I'll give him a hummer.
- Do you think that's what he wants?

692
00:57:32,080 --> 00:57:34,071
No.

693
00:57:35,920 --> 00:57:40,710
I don't know what he wants,
but I know I don't like being watched.

694
00:57:40,880 --> 00:57:45,431
No one's ever paid any attention
to what I did and I liked it fine.

695
00:57:45,600 --> 00:57:49,752
Where does he get off telling me
I disrespect myself? Fuck him!

696
00:57:49,920 --> 00:57:52,275
Look in the mirror, bozo!

697
00:57:59,240 --> 00:58:01,117
(GREETS THEM IN JAPANESE)

698
00:58:01,280 --> 00:58:03,077
Hello. Good to see you.

699
00:58:03,240 --> 00:58:05,231
I'm Lily.

700
00:58:06,360 --> 00:58:08,351
What's the deal?

701
00:58:10,320 --> 00:58:14,950
Hey. They come through several times
a year. Good to see you again!

702
00:58:15,120 --> 00:58:19,193
- Where am I supposed to eat?
- You're on your own today.

703
00:58:22,120 --> 00:58:23,678
Skip!

704
00:58:34,760 --> 00:58:38,548
- Hey, Doc.
- I want you to meet Skip. Skip, Lily.

705
00:58:38,720 --> 00:58:41,678
- It's a pleasure to meet you.
- Me too.

706
00:58:41,840 --> 00:58:44,035
- I was at your house.
- Oh?

707
00:58:44,200 --> 00:58:49,433
Upstairs with Doc. It's a very nice place.
I heard your shower.

708
00:58:55,280 --> 00:58:59,512
I see you going by on your board.
You're so young to be so...

709
00:58:59,680 --> 00:59:02,319
- What?
- So rich?

710
00:59:02,480 --> 00:59:04,436
So accomplished.

711
00:59:04,600 --> 00:59:08,388
I may be young, but Doc can tell you,
I'm very immature.

712
00:59:09,720 --> 00:59:13,952
- So, is this like a Japanese restaurant?
- I'd better go. Sorry.

713
00:59:14,120 --> 00:59:19,638
- That's a lot of people all at once.
- They pre-order. Choice of three entrées.

714
00:59:19,800 --> 00:59:21,711
What are they?

715
00:59:21,880 --> 00:59:25,156
Meatloaf, turkey quesadillas
and Salade Niçoise.

716
00:59:25,320 --> 00:59:29,757
- Salad Niçoise? I love Salade Niçoise!
- You do?

717
00:59:30,760 --> 00:59:34,639
- Well... Come on in.
- Far out!

718
00:59:41,240 --> 00:59:43,231
Dr. Mumford.

719
00:59:45,080 --> 00:59:50,677
- Dr. Delbanco. Nice to see you again.
- This is Dr. Sheeler, the other therapist here.

720
00:59:50,840 --> 00:59:54,071
- I've heard great things about you.
- Thank you.

721
00:59:54,240 --> 00:59:58,631
You never got back to me.
We'd like to take you out for a meal.

722
00:59:58,800 --> 01:00:03,635
- Kind of a professional welcome.
- Forgive me, please. We must do that.

723
01:00:03,800 --> 01:00:07,554
- When?
- I'll call you when I have my calendar.

724
01:00:07,720 --> 01:00:11,269
- What are you doing for lunch?
- Right now?

725
01:00:14,920 --> 01:00:18,754
...annihilation anxieties
because of a depriving mother,

726
01:00:18,920 --> 01:00:22,276
but either way,
no one can escape the fear of death.

727
01:00:22,440 --> 01:00:26,399
It is, as William James put it,
"the worm at the core".

728
01:00:26,560 --> 01:00:33,750
Try as we may to ignore our own mortality,
"the skull will grin in at the banquet".

729
01:00:37,600 --> 01:00:40,672
I've run on. We're here to talk about you.

730
01:00:40,840 --> 01:00:42,831
Are we?

731
01:00:43,720 --> 01:00:49,033
What Ernest means, I think, is
we're very interested in other methodology.

732
01:00:49,200 --> 01:00:52,636
We're great believers
in learning from each other.

733
01:00:52,800 --> 01:00:56,076
I've learned so much from Ernest.
Dr. Delbanco.

734
01:00:56,240 --> 01:00:57,798
And I from Phyllis.

735
01:00:57,960 --> 01:01:01,509
So, the University of Kentucky,
who runs the programme?

736
01:01:01,680 --> 01:01:05,355
My mentor was an amazing teacher
named Benton Mandlebaum.

737
01:01:05,520 --> 01:01:09,195
Died quite tragically
in the collapse of a gazebo.

738
01:01:10,040 --> 01:01:13,874
Your extended training
was at an institution in that area?

739
01:01:14,040 --> 01:01:15,917
Lots of institutions.

740
01:01:16,080 --> 01:01:22,076
My graduate advisor believed we should
experience prisons, clinics, halfway houses.

741
01:01:22,240 --> 01:01:26,233
For a while I was chief therapist
at a shopping mall.

742
01:01:26,400 --> 01:01:31,554
- Interesting approach. What was his name?
- Dorothy Fowler. Fantastic woman.

743
01:01:31,720 --> 01:01:35,395
She passed last year in a train wreck.

744
01:01:35,560 --> 01:01:37,516
Damned Amtrak.

745
01:01:43,160 --> 01:01:49,156
I trained in the east. Cornell. Whatever
anyone says, there are regional differences.

746
01:01:49,320 --> 01:01:52,756
I found the state certification exams
here harrowing.

747
01:01:52,920 --> 01:01:57,436
Oh, yeah, very tough, but I guess that's good.
Keep out the quacks.

748
01:01:57,600 --> 01:02:01,912
- Which examiner did you have?
- Wallace Franklin from Greensburg.

749
01:02:04,080 --> 01:02:05,877
That was a terrible thing.

750
01:02:06,040 --> 01:02:09,794
I don't know why hang-gliding
is even considered a sport.

751
01:02:13,080 --> 01:02:17,710
We're interested in new therapies.
How would you characterize your approach?

752
01:02:17,880 --> 01:02:22,158
- My approach?
- Yes, your particular approach.

753
01:02:23,720 --> 01:02:27,508
I don't have one, really.
Most of the time, I'm faking it.

754
01:02:27,680 --> 01:02:31,389
There's not much that can be done
about most problems.

755
01:02:31,560 --> 01:02:34,358
They're too deep-rooted
by the time I hear them.

756
01:02:34,520 --> 01:02:38,559
The most I can do, usually,
is look and listen real closely

757
01:02:38,720 --> 01:02:42,952
and try to catch some glimpse
of the secret life everybody's got.

758
01:02:43,120 --> 01:02:48,513
If I can get a sense of that, then maybe,
just maybe I can help them a little.

759
01:02:50,480 --> 01:02:52,198
I see.

760
01:02:53,120 --> 01:02:56,829
- The argument had nothing to do with it.
- What was it about?

761
01:02:57,000 --> 01:03:00,151
I'd ordered
the 100 greatest books ever written.

762
01:03:00,320 --> 01:03:02,959
- What are they?
- All the great writers.

763
01:03:03,120 --> 01:03:05,953
Shakespeare, Dickens, Moby Dick.
Those people.

764
01:03:06,120 --> 01:03:10,716
- 100 books?
- It's irrelevant. It had nothing to do with it.

765
01:03:10,880 --> 01:03:13,474
- What happened?
- We argued on Sunday.

766
01:03:13,640 --> 01:03:16,837
He went to work on Monday
and stayed in the city,

767
01:03:17,000 --> 01:03:20,675
but on Thursday,
when he normally comes home, he didn't.

768
01:03:20,840 --> 01:03:24,355
- He didn't call till Saturday.
- You were concerned.

769
01:03:24,520 --> 01:03:30,117
It's happened before.
I am shocked by how little I'm feeling.

770
01:03:30,280 --> 01:03:32,271
I don't understand this.

771
01:03:33,600 --> 01:03:37,513
I'll probably have
a complete depressoid collapse soon.

772
01:03:37,680 --> 01:03:40,114
- Won't I?
- Doubtful. What did he say?

773
01:03:40,280 --> 01:03:46,071
He said he wasn't coming back. He said
it hadn't worked for him for quite a while.

774
01:03:46,240 --> 01:03:48,629
Do you know what I regret the most?

775
01:03:48,800 --> 01:03:52,475
I am sorry I let him
make the kids take his name!

776
01:03:52,640 --> 01:03:56,428
He was an acquirer.
He liked to acquire things.

777
01:04:02,360 --> 01:04:05,830
You think that has
something to do with my problem.

778
01:04:06,000 --> 01:04:11,120
Ordering all those things.
Like I was on a campaign to out-acquire him.

779
01:04:11,280 --> 01:04:16,115
If I was just an acquisition to him
and he lost interest once he had me...

780
01:04:16,280 --> 01:04:19,636
Can't be it. It's too simple. And I still like it.

781
01:04:19,800 --> 01:04:24,920
This morning,
I ordered a marble turtle cheeseboard.

782
01:04:25,080 --> 01:04:30,359
Can I tell you something? You know how
assholes look at a woman with problems

783
01:04:30,520 --> 01:04:33,671
and say,
"What she needs is a good schtupping!"

784
01:04:33,840 --> 01:04:38,709
There may be something to that.
Jeremy didn't keep up his end.

785
01:04:39,960 --> 01:04:42,394
What difference does it make?

786
01:04:44,320 --> 01:04:46,356
Why do I feel elated?

787
01:04:47,560 --> 01:04:49,630
Am I in denial?

788
01:04:50,800 --> 01:04:53,075
You know what this feels like?

789
01:04:54,120 --> 01:04:57,954
- Time's up, but I've gotta get this out.
- Take your time.

790
01:04:58,120 --> 01:05:01,192
In high school, the thing that I wanted most,

791
01:05:01,360 --> 01:05:05,194
the thing I was desperately
in pursuit of, was a hall pass.

792
01:05:05,360 --> 01:05:11,117
I loved moving freely around the school
while everybody else was trapped in there.

793
01:05:11,280 --> 01:05:19,233
That's how I feel right now,
like I have some giant all-day hall pass.

794
01:05:28,880 --> 01:05:32,998
My God. Did it just get hot in here?

795
01:05:36,000 --> 01:05:41,632
I'll see you next time.
I'll probably be a basket case by then.

796
01:05:41,800 --> 01:05:46,794
- You can use the back if you like.
- No shame in getting a little therapy.

797
01:05:57,960 --> 01:05:59,871
Hello, Mr. Follett.

798
01:06:01,600 --> 01:06:03,591
Have a good session.

799
01:06:12,080 --> 01:06:13,399
Henry?

800
01:06:16,320 --> 01:06:18,311
Henry.

801
01:06:27,240 --> 01:06:29,231
Hey, Doc!

802
01:06:48,880 --> 01:06:51,189
Hey, Doc.

803
01:06:51,360 --> 01:06:54,432
Thanks, Jennifer. I'll take him from here.

804
01:06:56,440 --> 01:07:00,831
I'm glad you came.
I've never brought anyone down here before.

805
01:07:01,000 --> 01:07:02,991
I'm honored.

806
01:07:06,680 --> 01:07:08,079
It's just me, Dino.

807
01:07:17,880 --> 01:07:20,713
Skip, I've got a problem and I need advice.

808
01:07:20,880 --> 01:07:23,713
You want my advice?

809
01:07:23,880 --> 01:07:25,871
Far out!

810
01:07:36,320 --> 01:07:40,711
I hope nothing you're about to see
will shake your faith in me.

811
01:08:10,480 --> 01:08:12,471
Pretty creepy, huh?

812
01:08:14,360 --> 01:08:16,351
Are you totally disgusted?

813
01:08:17,200 --> 01:08:20,795
Skip, you're a visionary.
That can be a burden.

814
01:08:20,960 --> 01:08:22,916
This doesn't seem perverse?

815
01:08:23,080 --> 01:08:26,197
Somebody's gonna figure this out someday.

816
01:08:26,360 --> 01:08:32,754
<i>I'm really not comfortable here. </i>
<i>Can we go somewhere... more private?</i>

817
01:08:32,920 --> 01:08:36,595
- It's not gonna be me. I'm giving it up.
- Really?

818
01:08:36,760 --> 01:08:39,069
<i>Skip, you are so amazing!</i>

819
01:08:39,240 --> 01:08:44,075
It's all your fault. In the last 48 hours,
I've completely lost interest.

820
01:08:44,240 --> 01:08:47,471
- What did I do?
- Lily.

821
01:08:48,440 --> 01:08:50,749
Lily?

822
01:08:50,920 --> 01:08:53,480
- That's great! You and Lily?
<i>- Far out!</i>

823
01:08:53,640 --> 01:09:00,398
She doesn't know yet. Of the two of us,
I'm the only one in love, but I'm really stoked.

824
01:09:00,560 --> 01:09:02,869
Doc, how can I be of help to you?

825
01:09:03,040 --> 01:09:04,712
(MACHINE HUMS)

826
01:09:09,360 --> 01:09:11,476
Sorry.

827
01:09:11,640 --> 01:09:12,959
Wow.

828
01:09:14,040 --> 01:09:17,396
- I'm here for you, Doc.
- Skip...

829
01:09:17,560 --> 01:09:20,120
You know that it's improper, unethical,

830
01:09:20,280 --> 01:09:25,229
for a psychologist to have a romantic
relationship with one of his patients?

831
01:09:25,400 --> 01:09:29,234
- I guess that makes sense.
- Yes. Yes, it does.

832
01:09:32,920 --> 01:09:36,913
You've fallen in love
with one of your patients?

833
01:09:41,280 --> 01:09:45,159
- Doc, it's not me, is it?
- What?

834
01:09:47,160 --> 01:09:50,470
No, Skip, it's not you, but I like you a lot.

835
01:09:53,080 --> 01:09:55,355
Doc, what about this?

836
01:09:55,520 --> 01:09:58,432
You're not really a licensed psychologist.

837
01:10:00,360 --> 01:10:05,514
Hmm. I guess that doesn't help.
I see where you're going here. It's a mess.

838
01:10:06,280 --> 01:10:07,599
Yep.

839
01:10:07,760 --> 01:10:14,313
Everyone who could corroborate his story
has recently died some exotic death.

840
01:10:14,480 --> 01:10:17,870
- They're neither recent nor exotic.
- They are dead.

841
01:10:18,040 --> 01:10:21,237
And yes, personally, I find it a bit odd.

842
01:10:21,400 --> 01:10:25,188
It could happen.
The certification exams seem in order.

843
01:10:25,360 --> 01:10:30,070
What's easier than hacking into a state
computer and putting in numbers?

844
01:10:30,240 --> 01:10:33,755
- Maybe he didn't even take the exams.
- That's true.

845
01:10:33,920 --> 01:10:36,115
I don't know it's that easy...

846
01:10:36,280 --> 01:10:41,229
Doctor, it sounds like you've bought his story
hook, line and bull-twaddle!

847
01:10:41,400 --> 01:10:45,996
You seem more disposed to him
than I understand. Did I miss something?

848
01:10:46,160 --> 01:10:51,712
For God's sakes, we have no reason to
doubt him! Are we listening to Lionel now?!

849
01:10:54,560 --> 01:10:57,120
Phyllis... Phyllis...

850
01:10:57,280 --> 01:10:59,555
Phyllis.

851
01:10:59,720 --> 01:11:05,875
- I'm sorry. I didn't mean to shout.
- No, no. It is I who am sorry, Dr. Delbanco!

852
01:11:07,760 --> 01:11:13,312
I am sorry to have wasted your time...
with such...

853
01:11:14,240 --> 01:11:15,559
Phyllis...

854
01:11:40,440 --> 01:11:44,991
Stop it! He's a kid. I'm old enough to be his...

855
01:11:46,240 --> 01:11:48,595
...his big sister!

856
01:11:58,760 --> 01:12:04,198
- Dr. Mumford. Please come on in.
- Hello. I was wondering if Sofie was around.

857
01:12:04,360 --> 01:12:10,879
(TV) <i>The wood is different here. </i>
<i>It's not as consistent as it is in some events. </i>

858
01:12:11,040 --> 01:12:14,430
- Did you have a session?
- It's spur-of-the-moment.

859
01:12:14,600 --> 01:12:16,591
Look who's here!

860
01:12:16,760 --> 01:12:19,194
- You've met Sofie's mother.
- Mrs. Crisp.

861
01:12:19,360 --> 01:12:22,272
- We've met.
- And this is our son, Ben.

862
01:12:22,440 --> 01:12:27,673
- It's a real honor. Have a seat.
- Actually, I can't. Could I see Sofie?

863
01:12:27,840 --> 01:12:32,914
- I insist. I've been wanting to meet you.
- Sofie's not here.

864
01:12:33,080 --> 01:12:38,234
Her friend from the city took her to dinner.
First time she's been willing.

865
01:12:38,400 --> 01:12:41,437
We owe it to you. She has perked up a lot.

866
01:12:41,600 --> 01:12:45,309
- What do you want?
- There's something we need to talk about.

867
01:12:45,480 --> 01:12:46,959
- What?
- Elizabeth!

868
01:12:47,120 --> 01:12:49,111
- We have a right.
- We do not!

869
01:12:49,280 --> 01:12:54,070
- Keep it zipped, Ben!
- Is there something we need to know?

870
01:12:55,680 --> 01:13:00,708
Yes, I guess I should tell you.
I don't think I can treat Sofie any more.

871
01:13:00,880 --> 01:13:04,077
- Finally, some common sense.
- What do you mean?

872
01:13:04,240 --> 01:13:06,117
- You know.
- No, I don't.

873
01:13:06,280 --> 01:13:07,599
- You do.
- Tell me.

874
01:13:07,760 --> 01:13:12,356
- Go to hell. It's a bunch of nonsense.
- I'm telling you, stop.

875
01:13:12,520 --> 01:13:15,159
You're telling me? That's rich!

876
01:13:17,040 --> 01:13:18,837
I'd better go.

877
01:13:19,000 --> 01:13:22,913
Why can't you see Sofie?
The treatments are working.

878
01:13:23,080 --> 01:13:26,117
- The problem is...
- You're a big fake!

879
01:13:26,280 --> 01:13:29,636
You haven't got a clue
what's wrong with that girl.

880
01:13:29,800 --> 01:13:33,349
- Wow, you're something.
- Take a hike, Dr. Quack.

881
01:13:35,760 --> 01:13:38,149
Doctor, what is the problem?

882
01:13:39,200 --> 01:13:44,399
Problem? Uh, I guess there is no problem.

883
01:13:46,120 --> 01:13:51,752
- This friend, where did he take her?
- She. Roxy. I think they went to the Lantern.

884
01:13:51,920 --> 01:13:54,673
Oh, Roxy. Excellent.

885
01:13:55,480 --> 01:13:56,799
Roxy!

886
01:14:28,680 --> 01:14:30,671
Hi. Is Mr. Follett around?

887
01:14:33,760 --> 01:14:36,911
- What is it?
- It's a thought I had.

888
01:14:37,080 --> 01:14:39,071
Should I open it now?

889
01:14:44,200 --> 01:14:47,749
Let me say something.
I have no idea if this'll help.

890
01:14:47,920 --> 01:14:51,037
What exactly is it supposed to do?

891
01:14:51,200 --> 01:14:54,476
Some imagery is haunting you
and getting in your way.

892
01:14:54,640 --> 01:14:58,474
- I don't necessarily agree.
- But you did come to me.

893
01:14:58,640 --> 01:15:02,758
These images were burned
into your brain when you were young.

894
01:15:02,920 --> 01:15:07,789
If we could nail down the exact fantasies,
maybe you could get past them.

895
01:15:08,520 --> 01:15:13,275
- Anyway, I thought we'd try an experiment.
- The experiment's in here?

896
01:15:13,440 --> 01:15:14,759
Yep.

897
01:15:24,320 --> 01:15:30,509
I think this was a dumb idea. I just heard
myself and realized I'm unqualified for this.

898
01:15:30,680 --> 01:15:33,114
- Let's just forget it.
- Whoa, whoa.

899
01:15:33,280 --> 01:15:35,510
I wanna know what's in here.

900
01:15:35,680 --> 01:15:40,117
There's no reason to think
this is gonna have any impact on you.

901
01:15:41,240 --> 01:15:46,268
You don't know what you're talking about.
That's what I said all along.

902
01:15:46,440 --> 01:15:52,356
I can guarantee that looking at the Lost Ark
here won't mean diddly to me.

903
01:15:53,720 --> 01:15:58,919
But if you think I'll let you walk out
without seeing what's in this box,

904
01:15:59,080 --> 01:16:01,753
then you don't know Henry A Follett.

905
01:17:16,240 --> 01:17:18,390
- Mr. Follett?
- What?

906
01:17:18,560 --> 01:17:21,870
What is so important
I can't have five minutes?

907
01:17:22,040 --> 01:17:27,433
It's her, sir. You told me to get you
when she came to pick up her prescription.

908
01:17:30,920 --> 01:17:36,153
I'm sorry. I'm gonna have to...
I really appreciate what you...

909
01:17:37,440 --> 01:17:40,432
- I can't thank you enough.
- My pleasure.

910
01:17:43,920 --> 01:17:45,911
I'll see you on...

911
01:17:48,720 --> 01:17:50,039
Whatever.

912
01:17:57,080 --> 01:17:59,514
- Hello, Henry.
- Hello, Mrs. Brockett.

913
01:17:59,680 --> 01:18:01,750
Oh, please. Althea.

914
01:18:14,400 --> 01:18:18,552
When I was in high school,
we used to come up here and make out.

915
01:18:18,720 --> 01:18:21,553
- I liked to watch the sun go down.
- I like that.

916
01:18:21,720 --> 01:18:24,678
- Which thing?
- Either one.

917
01:18:27,240 --> 01:18:29,515
Why did you come to the house?

918
01:18:29,680 --> 01:18:33,070
I thought I had something to tell you,
but I didn't.

919
01:18:33,240 --> 01:18:37,233
- My brother said you were firing me.
- That's one way to put it.

920
01:18:37,400 --> 01:18:42,997
I know what changed your mind. My mother.
She's so horrible, you couldn't desert me.

921
01:18:43,160 --> 01:18:46,436
She made me appreciate your father.
He's my new hero.

922
01:18:46,600 --> 01:18:48,955
He was, actually, a hero.

923
01:18:49,120 --> 01:18:55,070
My dad, when he was in the coast guard,
risked himself to save three people.

924
01:18:55,240 --> 01:18:58,357
I know why you were gonna quit seeing me.

925
01:19:00,240 --> 01:19:05,189
You feel like a fake, an impostor,
as if you don't know what you are doing.

926
01:19:05,360 --> 01:19:10,388
Everybody feels that way sometimes,
like we're not who we're supposed to be.

927
01:19:10,560 --> 01:19:16,829
But, I have to tell you, Dr. Mumford,
you have been a tremendous help to me.

928
01:19:17,880 --> 01:19:22,510
- Yeah?
- I admire you. You're very insightful.

929
01:19:22,680 --> 01:19:24,989
I feel like you've seen me clearly.

930
01:19:25,160 --> 01:19:29,392
I never used to admit how horrible
my mother is. You made that possible.

931
01:19:29,560 --> 01:19:32,358
- That's good?
- Yes. And my ex-husband.

932
01:19:32,520 --> 01:19:34,795
He never accepted me for who I was.

933
01:19:34,960 --> 01:19:38,635
You've helped me understand
what a dick he is!

934
01:19:38,800 --> 01:19:42,793
You're shockingly honest.
That's what makes you great.

935
01:19:43,960 --> 01:19:48,954
I've never had a man treat me this way.
With you, I feel really listened to.

936
01:19:53,080 --> 01:19:58,154
Can I tell you something? It's embarrassing,
but I feel unguarded with you.

937
01:19:58,320 --> 01:20:00,675
Of course.

938
01:20:00,840 --> 01:20:06,472
Thanks to this therapy...
I now know what I am looking for.

939
01:20:06,640 --> 01:20:08,870
I need to find a man like you.

940
01:20:10,720 --> 01:20:14,269
Not one who's treating me, of course.

941
01:20:14,440 --> 01:20:18,558
And I'm gonna do it, damn it!
You have given me the confidence.

942
01:20:20,080 --> 01:20:23,470
Sofie... that makes me very happy.

943
01:20:25,960 --> 01:20:29,714
Doc, the dude is seriously deluded.
I said that to him.

944
01:20:29,880 --> 01:20:34,556
"If you think I'll do that shit for you,
you are seriously deluded. "

945
01:20:34,720 --> 01:20:38,633
- What did he say?
- He said, "Which we already knew. "

946
01:20:38,800 --> 01:20:43,828
- What did he want you to do?
- First he tells me to stop smoking.

947
01:20:44,000 --> 01:20:47,629
I told him, "Abso-fucking-lutely no",
as you can see.

948
01:20:47,800 --> 01:20:50,519
Then he says stop smoking dope. No again.

949
01:20:50,680 --> 01:20:54,434
Then he says he doesn't want me
going with any other guys.

950
01:20:54,600 --> 01:20:58,070
What balls on this guy!
Are we going steady? Jesus!

951
01:20:58,240 --> 01:21:02,153
- No again?
- I said I'd consider it.

952
01:21:02,720 --> 01:21:04,676
The last thing was insane.

953
01:21:04,840 --> 01:21:08,389
I don't know why,
but he wants me to give up magazines.

954
01:21:08,560 --> 01:21:11,836
- Really?
- I don't know if I can quit.

955
01:21:12,000 --> 01:21:15,470
We're gonna try it together,
like AA or something.

956
01:21:15,640 --> 01:21:21,317
I made him give up his. 22. No more
sneaking round with this fucking nut gun.

957
01:21:21,480 --> 01:21:24,790
- He agreed?
- He's pitiful, Doc, a goddamn puppy.

958
01:21:24,960 --> 01:21:27,838
I don't know how long I can put up with it.

959
01:21:28,000 --> 01:21:31,993
I've already got arms and legs.
I don't need another appendage.

960
01:21:32,160 --> 01:21:35,835
- (DOOR OPENS)
- Gotta go.

961
01:21:49,720 --> 01:21:51,597
- Hiya, Doc.
- Martin.

962
01:21:51,760 --> 01:21:54,832
- Did you straighten her out?
- How are you?

963
01:21:55,000 --> 01:22:00,279
Extremely excellent. Didn't you hear?
My family just got 500 times better.

964
01:22:01,160 --> 01:22:03,151
Let's go, Vanessa.

965
01:22:07,520 --> 01:22:11,513
- Dr. Mumford?
- I didn't notice you there. Can I help you?

966
01:22:11,680 --> 01:22:15,992
My name's Gilroy.
I'm from the State Certification Board.

967
01:22:16,160 --> 01:22:18,435
It's all right. It won't bite you.

968
01:22:18,600 --> 01:22:22,752
Under Civil Code 1294.67b,
you're entitled to be notified

969
01:22:22,920 --> 01:22:26,469
that your status and certification
are being reviewed.

970
01:22:26,640 --> 01:22:29,074
- Do you wanna come in?
- No, thanks.

971
01:22:29,240 --> 01:22:32,994
Plenty of time for that
when we're a little further along.

972
01:22:33,160 --> 01:22:34,559
Mr. Gilroy?

973
01:22:36,000 --> 01:22:39,356
- What brought this on?
- I'm not at liberty to say.

974
01:22:39,520 --> 01:22:44,878
Sometimes it's just routine. Sometimes
it's a complaint. We'll be in touch.

975
01:22:53,640 --> 01:22:57,519
When you said at lunch
about everybody having a secret life,

976
01:22:57,680 --> 01:22:59,716
something snapped inside me.

977
01:22:59,880 --> 01:23:04,476
I knew I could no longer continue
my relationship with Dr. Sheeler.

978
01:23:04,640 --> 01:23:07,279
Phyllis wasn't getting what she needed.

979
01:23:07,440 --> 01:23:12,468
What started as a genuine respect
for each other's professional abilities,

980
01:23:12,640 --> 01:23:15,074
and became a personal attraction,

981
01:23:15,240 --> 01:23:20,633
had somehow migrated
into a rather torrid sexual relationship that...

982
01:23:20,800 --> 01:23:26,636
I won't get into that today, although, if we
continue these sessions, and I hope we will,

983
01:23:26,800 --> 01:23:30,634
there are some aspects of that
I'd like to take a look at.

984
01:23:30,800 --> 01:23:34,395
I've listened to enough people
giving me the juicy...

985
01:23:34,560 --> 01:23:40,908
At any rate, I wanted to acknowledge the
catalyzing effect your comment had on me.

986
01:23:41,080 --> 01:23:46,950
I just hope it doesn't come roiling back
upon you like some dreadful undertow.

987
01:23:48,040 --> 01:23:50,713
- How do you mean?
- Well...

988
01:23:51,600 --> 01:23:55,718
You see, when I broke it off with Phyllis,
she was upset,

989
01:23:55,880 --> 01:24:01,432
and she became even more determined
to pursue certain doubts she's harbored.

990
01:24:01,600 --> 01:24:04,433
- What kind of doubts?
- About you.

991
01:24:05,320 --> 01:24:07,880
Your background, your qualifications.

992
01:24:08,040 --> 01:24:12,397
I'm afraid Phyllis somehow
got you mixed up in her fury with me

993
01:24:12,560 --> 01:24:15,711
and took the whole issue to the State Board.

994
01:24:16,800 --> 01:24:18,279
I see.

995
01:24:18,440 --> 01:24:20,874
- There's good news, though.
- What?

996
01:24:21,040 --> 01:24:24,510
Phyllis has decided
to pursue her practice in the city,

997
01:24:24,680 --> 01:24:27,990
which leaves you
the only psychologist in town.

998
01:24:28,160 --> 01:24:31,436
Dr. Sheeler is leaving Mumford?
Sorry to hear that.

999
01:24:31,600 --> 01:24:34,990
As you can imagine,
my own feelings are mixed...

1000
01:24:35,160 --> 01:24:37,628
unlike, I must say, those of my wife!

1001
01:24:42,400 --> 01:24:45,392
("TILL IT SHINES" BY BOB SEGER)

