01:25:07,680 --> 01:25:10,399
<i># Leave the inmates, free the guards</i>

1008
01:25:11,640 --> 01:25:16,634
<i># Deal me up another future</i>
<i>from some brand-new deck of cards</i>

1009
01:25:19,440 --> 01:25:22,750
<i># Take the chip off from my shoulder</i>

1010
01:25:23,480 --> 01:25:25,994
<i># Smooth out all the lines</i>

1011
01:25:27,320 --> 01:25:30,915
<i># Take me out among the rustling pines</i>

1012
01:25:33,840 --> 01:25:36,195
<i># Till it shines</i>

1013
01:25:38,040 --> 01:25:40,270
<i># Ah, till it shines</i>

1014
01:25:43,040 --> 01:25:45,190
<i># Like an echo down a canyon</i>

1015
01:25:46,960 --> 01:25:49,394
<i># Never coming back this clear</i>

1016
01:25:50,960 --> 01:25:53,394
<i># Lately I just judge the distance</i>

1017
01:25:53,560 --> 01:25:56,074
<i># Not the words I hear</i>

1018
01:25:58,760 --> 01:26:01,354
<i># I've been too long on these islands</i>

1019
01:26:02,840 --> 01:26:05,308
<i># I've been far too long alone</i>

1020
01:26:06,760 --> 01:26:09,035
<i># I've been too long without summer</i>

1021
01:26:09,200 --> 01:26:11,316
<i># In this winter home</i>

1022
01:26:14,680 --> 01:26:17,752
<i># Still, if we can make the effort</i>

1023
01:26:18,680 --> 01:26:20,750
<i># If we take the time</i>

1024
01:26:22,560 --> 01:26:25,916
<i># Maybe we can leave this much behind</i>

1025
01:26:29,240 --> 01:26:31,231
<i># Till it shines</i>

1026
01:26:32,920 --> 01:26:35,275
<i># Mmm, till it shines... #</i>

1027
01:26:42,200 --> 01:26:45,909
<i>Old man Sutter's young bride</i>
<i>had got me in hot water,</i>

1028
01:26:46,080 --> 01:26:49,277
<i>and now I was being dealt</i>
<i>the beating of my life. </i>

1029
01:26:49,440 --> 01:26:53,831
<i>If there'd just been two of them,</i>
<i>it would have been closer. </i>

1030
01:26:55,800 --> 01:27:01,557
<i>The landlady was good at quite a few things,</i>
<i>but doctoring wasn't one of 'em. </i>

1031
01:27:05,560 --> 01:27:08,472
<i>Lucky for me, one of the other boarders,</i>

1032
01:27:09,320 --> 01:27:14,678
<i>the broad who lived downstairs</i>
<i>in the front room... was a nurse. </i>

1033
01:27:21,680 --> 01:27:26,515
<i>She had ways to make you feel better</i>
<i>they didn't teach in nursing school. </i>

1034
01:27:37,080 --> 01:27:41,437
I'm very happy for you.
I feel like we're making real progress.

1035
01:27:41,600 --> 01:27:45,639
Me, too, Doc. I can't tell you
what that package meant to me.

1036
01:28:05,560 --> 01:28:07,551
(OUTER DOOR CLOSES)

1037
01:28:16,560 --> 01:28:19,597
- Hi.
- I need to talk to you... Doctor.

1038
01:28:19,760 --> 01:28:22,228
- Can I come in?
- Of course.

1039
01:28:31,320 --> 01:28:33,959
We haven't met here since the first time.

1040
01:28:34,120 --> 01:28:38,272
This is how a real professional
and his client see each other.

1041
01:28:38,440 --> 01:28:44,709
It might have been more appropriate if we
had followed a more traditional approach.

1042
01:28:44,880 --> 01:28:46,632
Is something wrong, Sofie?

1043
01:28:46,800 --> 01:28:50,315
- Something is very wrong, Dr. Mumford.
- You're upset.

1044
01:28:50,480 --> 01:28:54,632
How intuitive. That must take
years of training right there.

1045
01:28:54,800 --> 01:29:00,432
- Maybe you can guess what has upset me.
- Is it something you've heard about me?

1046
01:29:00,600 --> 01:29:05,799
No, it is not something... Is there something
I should have heard about you?

1047
01:29:05,960 --> 01:29:08,997
Why don't you tell me what's on your mind?

1048
01:29:10,720 --> 01:29:12,711
- May I?
- Sure.

1049
01:29:15,960 --> 01:29:18,793
I'm just gonna come right out and say this.

1050
01:29:18,960 --> 01:29:22,999
That's what your shrink is for,
to say what's bothering you.

1051
01:29:23,160 --> 01:29:26,118
First of all,
I have been feeling much better.

1052
01:29:26,280 --> 01:29:30,273
I don't know if the syndrome is over,
or if it's run its course,

1053
01:29:30,440 --> 01:29:33,398
but I feel 100% better
than when I came to you.

1054
01:29:33,560 --> 01:29:35,198
- I'm glad.
- Given that...

1055
01:29:35,640 --> 01:29:40,077
- I'm not going to judge things properly.
- I don't follow you.

1056
01:29:40,240 --> 01:29:43,710
I'm saying
that since I am doing so much better,

1057
01:29:43,880 --> 01:29:49,000
which I attribute to you, I am liable
to misinterpret some of my feelings.

1058
01:29:49,160 --> 01:29:52,675
The point is this: I am not a blank page.

1059
01:29:52,840 --> 01:29:56,674
I did not just fall off the turnip truck.
Know what I mean?

1060
01:29:56,840 --> 01:30:00,958
I know a little about psychology.
I took three courses in college.

1061
01:30:01,120 --> 01:30:04,351
None were above the 200 level,
but I took them.

1062
01:30:04,520 --> 01:30:08,229
- And one concept I remember very well.
- What was that?

1063
01:30:09,000 --> 01:30:10,877
Transference.

1064
01:30:12,800 --> 01:30:17,351
- Transference.
- Yes, and that is what I have got right now.

1065
01:30:17,520 --> 01:30:23,072
I have taken my feelings of gratitude
and relief and transferred them onto you.

1066
01:30:23,240 --> 01:30:26,232
I have taken
all those warm, grateful emotions

1067
01:30:26,400 --> 01:30:29,073
and confused them with feelings for you,

1068
01:30:29,240 --> 01:30:31,674
so now I am under the delusion that...

1069
01:30:35,120 --> 01:30:37,111
...I am in love with you.

1070
01:30:42,640 --> 01:30:44,631
Hello?

1071
01:30:46,520 --> 01:30:48,112
Hello.

1072
01:30:49,760 --> 01:30:54,117
You can understand why I have
serious questions about your methods.

1073
01:30:54,280 --> 01:30:58,717
Obviously, it's much more likely
that I'll have confusion about this

1074
01:30:58,880 --> 01:31:02,429
when your idea of treatment
is to go walking in the woods

1075
01:31:02,600 --> 01:31:05,239
and do these highly romantic activities!

1076
01:31:05,400 --> 01:31:09,029
We had a paper route together,
for God's sake!

1077
01:31:11,720 --> 01:31:14,553
Do you understand how I might be resentful,

1078
01:31:14,720 --> 01:31:19,840
knowing that this so-called love I'm feeling
is totally bogus

1079
01:31:20,000 --> 01:31:22,878
and just a pathetic case of...

1080
01:31:23,960 --> 01:31:25,632
...transference?

1081
01:31:27,080 --> 01:31:28,593
Yes.

1082
01:31:35,240 --> 01:31:39,233
Maybe you ought to think
about how you're gonna fix this.

1083
01:31:41,880 --> 01:31:45,475
And when you do, please get back to me.

1084
01:32:03,360 --> 01:32:04,918
(DOG BARKS)

1085
01:32:05,080 --> 01:32:06,832
Ainge.

1086
01:32:07,000 --> 01:32:08,433
Doc?

1087
01:32:08,600 --> 01:32:10,511
Lily?

1088
01:32:11,320 --> 01:32:15,552
Doc... I don't want you to be mad at Skip.

1089
01:32:16,560 --> 01:32:18,312
He told you?

1090
01:32:18,480 --> 01:32:22,837
Skip and I wouldn't have got together
if not for you. That's a big deal.

1091
01:32:23,000 --> 01:32:27,994
- You'd have met in some shower eventually.
- I wanna give you something.

1092
01:32:28,960 --> 01:32:31,679
- OK.
- Here it is.

1093
01:32:31,840 --> 01:32:35,071
Some advice. Do the hard thing.

1094
01:32:35,840 --> 01:32:39,992
- That's it?
- Clean up the mess, no matter what it takes.

1095
01:32:42,680 --> 01:32:49,028
- What it might take is doing time.
- Too bad. That's tough. I mean it.

1096
01:32:49,200 --> 01:32:53,318
I'm not unsympathetic,
but Skip says you're in love.

1097
01:32:55,400 --> 01:32:58,915
- Yep.
- Then it's worth it.

1098
01:33:05,240 --> 01:33:07,231
I'll tell her tonight.

1099
01:33:17,200 --> 01:33:19,839
<i>Tonight on "Unsolved Mysteries"... </i>

